    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You must verify that the scaffolding is built on a solid, level foundation, or you'll be standing on a wobbling platform that could easily tip over, much like a house built on a swamp. Before the first guy steps on, you need to check that the base plates are securely bolted to the ground and that the outriggers are fully extended and locked down, acting as the giant legs of a goblin that keeps the whole structure from falling into the mud.\n\nNext, inspect every single rung and platform for any signs of rust, cracks, or loose bolts, because a single broken rung is like a goblin's missing tooth—it's a critical weakness that could let a worker fall through the floor. You must also ensure that all guardrails and toe boards are in place and that the scaffolding is free from any obstructions, debris, or foreign objects that could get caught in the moving parts, much like a goblin trying to hide in a tight space.\n\nFinally, make sure that the scaffolding is not overloaded with too many workers or equipment, as a goblin can't carry too much weight without breaking his own bones, and a full scaffold is just as dangerous. If you find any of these issues, you",
